  "buggy_files": ["drivers/ata/libata-core.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["ata_device_blacklist"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Samsung 860 EVO SSD is not listed in the ata_device_blacklist array in drivers/ata/libata-core.c. The bug report shows that the device experiences 20-30 second lockups and FPDMA QUEUED command timeouts during fstrim operations. This is identical to the known issue with Samsung SSD 840 and 850 models, which are already listed in the blacklist (lines 4562-4565) with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag set. Without this flag, the kernel attempts to use queued TRIM commands on the 860 EVO, which the device doesn't properly handle. The ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv() function (line 2197-2224) checks for this horkage flag and disables queued TRIM support by clearing the DSM_TRIM bit in the device's NCQ Send/Recv commands. The fix requires adding an entry for 'Samsung SSD 860*' to the ata_device_blacklist array with the same horkage flags (ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM | ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM) used for the 840 and 850 models. This will prevent the kernel from attempting queued TRIM operations on this problematic hardware."
}

